@group greengrass
@endpoint PUT /greengrass/groups/{GroupId}/role
@desc Associates a role with a group. Your Greengrass core will use the role to access AWS cloud services. The role's permissions should allow Greengrass core Lambda functions to perform actions against the cloud.
@required {GroupId: str, RoleArn: str}
@returns(200) {AssociatedAt: str?}

@endpoint PUT /greengrass/servicerole
@desc Associates a role with your account. AWS IoT Greengrass will use the role to access your Lambda functions and AWS IoT resources. This is necessary for deployments to succeed. The role must have at least minimum permissions in the policy ''AWSGreengrassResourceAccessRolePolicy''.
@required {RoleArn: str}
@returns(200) {AssociatedAt: str?}

@endpoint POST /greengrass/definition/connectors
